RACE.FOOTNOTES: INTRICATE tracked along the inside, loomed a danger while pursuing from the pocket with run around the far turn, smoothly split the leaders two wide, gained an advantage in upper stretch, surged clear at the furlong grounds and was ridden out under moderate urging. THORPEDO ANNA hopped slightly and broke slow, recovered to track in the four to five path and outside of foes around the first turn, stalked three wide while inching closer around the far turn, bid in the four path entering the lane, but was outkicked by an inner rival in upper stretch, edged place in the final furlong and lasted from an outer bidder late. GIN GIN bumped an inner rival causing a chain-reaction at the start, pursued from midpack two wide and between horses, chased in the two path around the far turn and failed to menace. PURLOIN broke a step slow and took contact from an outer rival at the start, lacked speed in the two path, shifted out to the four path entering the lane and made little impact. HERE'S THE SPIDER received a bump from an outer rival at the start, bumped an inner foe and steadied back in the process, trailed in the three path, floated to the five path entering the lane and was outrun. WEST SUNSET tugged clear in the three path around the first turn, settled into stride before saving ground showing the way from chasing rivals around the far turn, but faltered inside of a trio of bidders in upper stretch and caved through the final furlong.
